      <item>
        <title>No referral links policy</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[@moparisthebest Moparisthebest]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
          <p><a href="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/u/moparisthebest">@moparisthebest</a> wrote:</p>
          <blockquote>
              <p>The rule states that there can be no misleading links.</p>
<p>That means you can’t do something like:<br>
<a href="http://google.com/r?ref=somereferralnumber" data-bbcode="true" rel="nofollow noopener"><br>
Click here for 1 million RS2 gp.</a></p>
<p>But if you want to put a blatent referral link in your signature there is nothing wrong with it, as long as the site has been approved that is.</p>
          </blockquote>
          <p><a href="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/t/no-referral-links-policy/144597/12">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
